.TH "memchr" 9 "memchr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
memchr \- Find a character in an area of memory.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" memchr
.BI "(const void *s "  ","
.BI "int c "  ","
.BI "size_t n "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "s" 12
The memory area
.IP "c" 12
The byte to search for
.IP "n" 12
The size of the area.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
returns the address of the first occurrence of \fIc\fP, or NULL
if \fIc\fP is not found
